  "texts": [
    "The color represents instead different values of the parameter ν 2 from 0 to 2ν 1.",
    "For reference, we also flag using a red dot the pair of exponents related to the parameters used in Fig. 4a.",
    "We can immediately notice how the 1st-and 2nd-order Heaps' exponents increase as ν 1 gets larger.",
    "More interestingly, we observe the combined role of the two parameters.",
    "For each curve, by increasing ν 2, therefore triggering new links in the network, the difference between β 1 and β 2 becomes larger, and the point (β 1, β 2) moves away from the bisector, in a way that depends on the specific value of ν 1."
